This paper deals with the problem of learning from pairwise supervision data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper specifically focuses on learning from Similar (S) and Dissimilar (D) pairs, which is a sub-problem of supervised learning. The paper also discusses the issue of label noise, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of data cleaning and preprocessing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the issue of privacy-sensitive domains, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms to learn from noisy pairwise data, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
